{{Quote|Dice Ibegon was a Force-sensitive Lamproid and a member of the Rebel Alliance.|An entry in an artist's journal restored and expanded by the Graf Archive|<ref name="Alien Archive">''[[Star Wars: Alien Archive]]''</ref>}}
'''Dice Ibegon''' was a [[Force-sensitive]] [[Lamproid]], a member of the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic]], and the lover of [[Lak Sivrak]], whom she convinced to join the Alliance. She was a patron of [[Chalmun's Spaceport Cantina]] on the [[planet]] [[Tatooine]] in [[1 BBY]] and sat at a table across from the [[Pacithhip]] named [[Ketwol]].

==Biography==
{{Listen3|Ibegon-Ketwol-Soundboard.flac|Dice Ibegon speaking Lamproid and Ketwol speaking Shimiese|{{SWArchive|url=play/online-activities/soundboards|text=Star Wars: Soundboards|int=Star Wars Soundboard}}}}
[[File:Ibegon-Labria-Ketwol-ANH.png|thumb|right|300px|Dice Ibegon sat with Ketwol.]]
Dice Ibegon was a [[Lamproid]] [[Gender|female]] who served in the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic]]<ref name="SWFC" /> during the [[Galactic Civil War]] against the [[Galactic Empire]]. After she met the [[Shistavanen]] [[Lak Sivrak]], a former Imperial [[scout]],<ref name="Sivrak">{{ForceCollection|Lak Sivrak|star=1}}</ref> the pair became lovers and Ibegon convinced Sivrak to join her in the Alliance.<ref name="SWFC" />

In [[1 BBY]],<ref name="Atlas">{{FilmDate|IV|1}}</ref> Ibegon spent [[time]] in [[Chalmun's Spaceport Cantina]] in the [[city]] of [[Mos Eisley]] on the [[desert]] [[planet]] [[Tatooine]]. She sat at a table in one of the [[cantina]]'s booths with the [[Pacithhip]]<ref name="CL">[[Star Wars: Complete Locations (2016)|''Star Wars: Complete Locations'']]</ref> [[Ketwol]],<ref name="Card Trader">{{SWCT|set=Alien Underground|cardname=Ketwol}}</ref> who was sharing a jigger or [[Merenzane Gold]] with the [[Defel]]<ref name="CL" /> [[Arleil Schous]]<ref name="AEYNTK">''[[Star Wars: Absolutely Everything You Need to Know, Updated and Expanded]]''</ref> and the [[Devaronian]] [[Kardue'sai'Malloc]].<ref name="Labria">{{ForceCollection|Kardue'sai'Malloc|star=2}}</ref> Ibegon spoke to Ketwol in [[Lamproid (language)|Lamproid]], with the Pacithip responding in [[Shimiese]],<ref name="Language">{{SWKidsYouTube|series=Star Wars By the Numbers|text=Every Language in Star Wars Movies|video=CZp8Civk2co|nolive=1}}</ref> shortly before an altercation at the cantina's bar<ref name="ANH">{{Film|IV}}</ref> resulted in the local [[moisture farmer]] [[Luke Skywalker]] being thrown into the table next to Ibegon's group by the criminals [[Cornelius Evazan]] and [[Ponda Baba]].<ref name="CL" />

Ibegon was mentioned in an [[Unidentified artist|artist's]] [[Unidentified artist's journal|journal]], which was restored, expanded, and displayed by the [[Graf Archive]]<ref name="Alien Archive" /> at some point after [[34 ABY]].<ref name="Year">{{AlienArchiveJournalDate}}</ref>

==Personality and traits==
Dice Ibegon was a [[Force-sensitive]] Lamproid with [[Color|brown]] skin.<ref name="SWFC" />

==Behind the scenes==
Dice Ibegon first appeared in the [[1977]] [[original trilogy]] film, [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|Star Wars: Episode IV ''A New Hope'']].<ref name="ANH" /> The character was portrayed by [[Phil Tippett]].<ref name="Archeology">{{YouTube|video=ElyMaaAFLKU|text=The Star Wars Cantina PT. 2 &#124; Full Panel #indianacomicconvention #tomspinadesigns #starwarshistory|channel=@FanXComicConventions|name=FanX Comic Conventions|date=2025-05-03}}</ref>

